<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">King <persName type="from">George VI</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d185fn1">Sent by the United States Military
                                Attaché, London, via Army channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-26">26 July
                                1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>From the King to President Roosevelt personal and most secret.</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">President Roosevelt</hi>: I greatly hope that
                            throughout your forthcoming meeting with my Prime Minister at Quebec,
                            you and he will occupy the Governor-General’s quarters in the
                            Citadel.</p>
                        <p>Lord Athlone tells me he will be delighted to arrange for them to be put
                            at your joint disposal. As he himself will be leaving Ottawa on <pb facs="0516" n="402" xml:id="pg_402"/> August 8th for a long planned
                            tour of the northwest, he regrets that it will not be possible for him
                            to meet you in Quebec as he would otherwise have wished to do.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi> R. I.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>